Linux Hardening

Update Linux
  apt-get update

Upgrade Linux 
  apt-get upgrade -y

Locking the boot directory
  nano /etc/fstab
    +LABEL=/boot  /boot  ext2 defaults, ro  1 2
  chown root:root /etc/fstab

Permissions for secure boot
  chown root:root /etc/grub.conf
  chmod og-rwx /etc/grub.conf

Require Authentication for single-user mode
  sed -i "/SINGLE/s/sushell/sulogin/" /etc/sysconfig/init 
  sed -i "/PROMPT/s/yes/no/" /etc/sysconfig/init

Disable USB usage
  nano /etc/modprobe.d/blacklist.conf
  blacklist usb_storage
  nano /etc/rc.local
    +modprobe -r usb_storage
    +exit 0

Checking Installed Packages
  apt-cache pkgnames

Removing Unneccessary Services
  EXAMPLES : Telnet, RSH, NIS, TFTP, TALK

Checking Open Ports
  netstat -antp

Secure/Harden SSH
  1. Options of sshd_config file
    a. Change port #
        nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config
    b.  Additional Options
        Protocol2
        IgnoreRhosts to yes
        HostbasedAuthentication no
        PermitEmptyPasswords no
        X11Forwarding no
        MaxAuthTries 5
        Ciphers aes128-ctr,aes192-ctr,aes256-ctr
        ClientAliveInterval 900 
        ClientAliveCountMax 0
        UsePAM yes
    c. Set permissions on the sshd_config file so only root can modify
        chown root:root /etc/ssh/sshd_config
        chmod 600 /etc/ssh/sshd_config

  2. Disable root login remotely through SSH 
      PermitRootLogin no
      AllowUsers [username] 
  
  
